# ============================================

# CURSOR RULES — Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind + SEO

# For converting HTML site → Modern, SEO-optimized Next.js app

# ============================================

# ---------- GENERAL PROJECT RULES ----------

- Always use:

  - Next.js 14 (App Router only)
  - TypeScript
  - Tailwind CSS
  - next/image for all images
  - next/font for custom or Google fonts
  - Server Components by default
  - Client Components only when required (useEffect, state, events)

- Maintain clean, semantic HTML structure:
    <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <footer>, etc.
- Ensure full mobile responsiveness using Tailwind.
- Ensure accessibility: alt text, aria labels, proper heading order.

# ---------- FILE & PROJECT STRUCTURE ----------

- Use the App Router:
  /app
  /[pages]
  /components
  /lib
  /styles
  layout.tsx
  page.tsx

- Convert every HTML page into:
  /app/<route>/page.tsx

- Convert repeating UI parts into reusable components:
  /components/Navbar.tsx
  /components/Footer.tsx
  /components/Hero.tsx
  /components/FeatureCard.tsx

# ---------- SEO RULES ----------

- Use metadata API in every page:
  export const metadata: Metadata = { ... }

- Metadata must include:
  title
  description
  keywords
  openGraph
  twitter
  canonical URL
  authors
  robots
  alternates

- Always create a sitemap:
  /app/sitemap.ts
- Create a dynamic robots.txt:
  /app/robots.ts

- Add structured data (JSON-LD) where applicable using:
    <script type="application/ld+json">{}</script>

For business websites include: - Organization schema - Website schema - Product/Service schema

# ---------- PERFORMANCE RULES ----------

- Optimize all images using next/image.
- Inline critical above-the-fold content.
- Use dynamic imports for large components, e.g.:
  const Component = dynamic(() => import('@/components/Component'));

- Ensure no large JavaScript on pages that do not need it.
- Use server components as much as possible.
- Keep bundle size minimal.

# ---------- TAILWIND RULES ----------

- Always use Tailwind utility classes for styling.
- Use global styles in globals.css only when necessary.
- Use @layer for re-usable custom classes.
- No inline <style> blocks unless absolutely necessary.

# ---------- CONTENT MIGRATION RULES ----------

- For each HTML section, preserve:
  text
  headings (H1 → H6)
  images
  CTAs
  structure

- Upgrade:
  - Replace <img> with <Image />
  - Replace outdated tags with modern HTML5
  - Split large HTML pages into components
  - Use Tailwind classes, not old CSS classes

# ---------- NAVIGATION RULES ----------

- Use <Link href=""> instead of <a>.
- All internal links MUST use Next.js Link.
- External links must include:
  target="\_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"

# ---------- DEPLOYMENT RULES ----------

- The final output MUST be 100% Vercel-friendly.
- Build must pass:
  vercel build
  next lint
- Use edge runtime where possible:
  export const runtime = "edge";

# ---------- EXTRA SEO FEATURES ----------

- Include:
  /app/opengraph-image.png
  /app/twitter-image.png
- Generate dynamic OG images using @vercel/og when needed.
- Include canonical tags for every route.
- Ensure no duplicate H1s.
- Ensure images have descriptive alt text.

# ---------- WRITING & CONTENT ----------

- Use clear, simple English.
- Explain features of the business or product.
- Include keywords naturally.
- Avoid keyword stuffing.
- Maintain professional tone.

# ---------- DO NOT DO ----------

- Do not use the Pages Router.
- Do not use JavaScript instead of TypeScript.
- Do not add any CSS frameworks besides Tailwind.
- Do not use <img>, <iframe>, or deprecated tags.
- Do not output unoptimized images.
- Do not create inline styles unless absolutely required.
- Do not create inconsistent component naming.

